### 0. Definitions (summary)
“Software” means original code/resources/docs in this repository under the
authors’ copyright, excluding third-party components. “Commercial use”
means use primarily for direct or indirect economic gain (sale, paid
distribution, commercial embedding, for-profit services, ad-monetized apps
whose primary function is this Software, etc.). “Source-available” means
providing complete corresponding source in a way a skilled person can
reasonably obtain and rebuild. “Encrypted/obfuscated distribution” means
publishing only encrypted, packed, or deliberately unreadable forms without
also making source available.

### 1. Grant
Subject to this License: non-commercial use, copying, modification, and
redistribution of the Software and derivatives, with a limited,
non-exclusive, non-transferable, terminable license. All other rights reserved.

### 2. Restrictions
Without prior written consent: no commercial use; no encrypted/obfuscated
distribution without source-available compliance; no removal of notices;
no trademark/endorsement confusion regarding “Lumin” / “Lumin SSH”.

### 3. Redistribution
Must include this License, preserve notices, keep source available, describe
material changes, and comply with third-party licenses.

### 4. Termination
Material breach terminates your rights. Downstream recipients who received
copies lawfully and are not themselves in breach are not automatically cut off.

### 5. Third parties
Third-party OSS remains under its own licenses. This License does not alter
those terms and applies only to the authors’ original Software.

### 6. Disclaimer
AS IS, no warranties. Liability limited to the maximum extent permitted by law.

